title: App crash with 'NSInvalidArgumentException' on 'Scan QR code' tap from Wallet [iOS]
body:
***Type***: Bug

***Summary***: Navigating to 'Wallet' -> 'Chose recipient' -> 'Scan QR code' sporadically ends up with the app crash. TF logs says that's because of: 
`*** Terminating app due to uncaught exception 'NSInvalidArgumentException', reason: '*** -[AVCaptureMetadataOutput setMetadataObjectTypes:] Unsupported type found - use -availableMetadataObjectTypes'
`

#### Expected behavior
No crash on 'Scan QR code' tap when choose recipient in Wallet.
#### Actual behavior
Crash on 'Scan QR code' tap when choose recipient in Wallet.

### Reproduction
- Install fresh build
- Open Status and create a new account
- Navigate to 'Wallet' -> 'Send transaction' screen
- Tap 'Specify recipients'
- Tap 'Scan QR code'

### Additional Information
* Status version: Develop (22nd of February) 0.9.11d714
* Operating System: iOS

#### Logs

https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/7710478/sessions/9/?accessToken=VlnrwnBYcsVOzisjhokN8afk19Y
Note: the #3417 issue has the same error. Will keep an eye on that one after #3417 is fixed.
